For digital inclusion in Nigeria, Itel has partnered Airtel Nigeria for customers to access 4G at an affordable rate. During a press briefing in Lagos, the firms noted that the collaboration was driven by need to migrate 2G and 3G users to 4G. Marketing Manager, West Africa 1, Itel, Oke Umurhohwo, observed that the firm has presence in 50 countries across Africa, Middle East, Central Eastern Europe and South Asia. Director, Cooperate Communications and Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) Airtel, Adefemi Adeniran, said the partnership would accelerate his organisationâ€™s global desire for digital penetration. Marketing Director, Airtel Nigeria, Ismail Adeshina, submitted that the collaboration would mutually benefit customers.